partDescription: Airframe Pro™ Helmet - Warbird™ - Blue - XS
bullet1: Increased angle of attack designed to maintain visibility and stability
bullet2: Compressed compact shape
bullet3: Sculpted neckline avoids jacket or suit interference
bullet4: Carbon fiber Dyneema® and fiberglass composite shell for extra strength; Construct helmet has a rough imperfect finish
bullet5: Oversized intake and exhaust ports vent hot air and help prevent fogging
bullet6: Removable molded breath deflector reduces shield fogging
bullet7: Icon Optics™ shield
bullet9: Nine intake and five exhaust vents
bullet10: Rear spoiler for reduced helmet buffeting
bullet11: Fully removable Hydra-Dry™ moisture-wicking interior
bullet12: Construct has a naked amber weave finish that has been coated in rich gloss clear-coat
bullet13: All World Standard meets or exceeds the following: DOT FMVSS 218 (USA) ECE 22-05 (Europe) SAI AS1698 (Australia) & SG (Japan) safety and testing standards

bullet9: Does not ship with SAI PSC or MFJ certification stickers unless purchased from an authorized dealer in that country

bullet8: Does not ship with SAI PSC or MFJ certification stickers unless purchased from an authorized dealer in that country

bullet1: Injection-molded polycarbonate shell for strength
bullet2: Multiple oversized intake and exhaust ports are strategically placed to keep you cool and comfortable including four intake vents MX-inspired chinbar vent and two exhaust ports that channel air between the comfort liner and the protective energy-absorbing EPS foam liner
bullet3: Quick-change fog-free outer Fliteshield™ keeps debris away while the internal interchangeable DropShield™ keeps the sun in check with a flip of a switch
bullet4: Removable molded breath deflector and chin curtain
bullet5: Moisture-wicking Hydradry™ interior is fully removable and washable
bullet6: Both wind drag and weight are decreased by sculpting the traditional neckline of the Airflite™ to avoid jacket or suit interference
bullet7: Meets DOT FMVSS 218 (US) ECE 22-05 (Europe) SAI AS1698:2006 (Australia) and SPC (Japan) safety and testing standards
bullet8: Does not ship with SAI PSC or MFJ certification stickers unless purchased from an authorized dealer in that country
bullet9: Includes Clear Fliteshield™ and Dark Smoke Internal Dropshield™; Dark Smoke Fliteshield™ sold separately

bullet1: Injection-molded polycarbonate shell for strength
bullet2: Multiple oversized intake and exhaust ports are strategically placed to keep you cool and comfortable including four intake vents MX-inspired chinbar vent and two exhaust ports that channel air between the comfort liner and the protective energy-absorbing EPS foam liner
bullet3: Quick-change fog-free outer FliteShield™ keeps debris away while the internal interchangeable DropShield™ keeps the sun in check with a flip of a switch
bullet4: Removable molded breath deflector and chin curtain
bullet5: Moisture-wicking Hydradry™ interior is fully removable and washable
bullet6: Both wind drag and weight are decreased by sculpting the traditional neckline of the Airflite™ to avoid jacket or suit interference
bullet7: Meets DOT FMVSS 218 (US) ECE 22-05 (Europe) SAI AS1698:2006 (Australia) and PSC (Japan) safety and testing standards
bullet8: Does not ship with SAI PSC or MFJ certification stickers unless purchased from an authorized dealer in that country
bullet9: Includes Clear Fliteshield™ and Dark Smoke Internal Dropshield™; Dark Smoke Fliteshield™ sold separately
